article.headline: Stephen F.Austin 62, Grambling St. 41
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas -- Jordan Glynn's double-double paced Stephen F. Austin to a 62-41 victory over Grambling State on Friday night in the Lumberjack Classic. Glynn paired 15 rebounds with 12 points for the Lumberjacks (5-2). Eddie Williams added 13 points and Jereal Scott 11. Yondarius Johnson led the Tigers (1-8) with 10 points. Stephen F. Austin scored the first nine points before Johnson's 3-pointer got Grambling on the board. The first-half lead maxed out at 15, and the Lumberjacks led 31-19 at the break. Stephen F. Austin ripped off the first 12 points of the second half -- four each by Scott, Glynn and Williams -- for a 43-19 advantage. It was never close thereafter. The Lumberjacks had 13 steals and forced 22 turnovers. They outshot Grambling 40.4 percent (23 of 57) to 32.7 percent (18 of 55).
